  "rationale": "This supervisor prioritizes rapid marker acquisition and approach while ensuring obstacle avoidance and safe recovery. It uses helper states for action commitment, marker tracking, and recovery. After obstacle encounters, it always passes through a scan/search state before resuming exploration. Marker tracking is prioritized when marker_seen is detected, and marker_lost triggers a scan. Marker_close always leads to a terminal stop state. Oscillation is avoided by preferring fixed rotation directions for left/right obstacles.",
